pr_title: Milestone 1.1 (Improving the lesson creation experience): Create the new domain objects
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of N/A.
2. This PR creates the following new domain objects:
- ExplorationMetadata (frontend)
- StateVersionHistory (frontend)
- ExplorationMetadata (backend)
- StateVersionHistory (backend)
- Renames the existing exploration metadata domain object in the frontend to exploration search result.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

No proof of changes needed because this PR just adds domain objects.

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI in any of the files listed in rtl_css.py (i.e, those that have
a separate .rtl.css file for styling), make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Milestone 1.2 (Improving the lesson creation experience): Create the new storage model and implement its lifecycle
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of N/A.
2. This PR does the following:
- Adds a third party python library called deepdiff to facilitate recursive comparison of dictionaries.
- Creates the ExplorationVersionHistoryModel.
- Handles the CRUD operations for the ExplorationVersionHistoryModel.
- Handles the wipeout process of the ExplorationVersionHistoryModel.

- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

<!--

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof

-->

-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.

This makes it extendable.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 25, 4, 52, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nithusha21', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 906635176, 'comment_body': 'Make this scalable by looping over the list and deleting all those properties mentioned in the list', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 25, 4, 53, 34, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nithusha21', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 906635308, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
            if diff_dict is not None:
```
Or whatever the expected return is for no diff', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 25, 4, 54, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nithusha21', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 906635519, 'comment_body': "You can make it a set() and keep inserting. It'll automatically exclude duplicates and you can cast it to a list before returning.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 25, 4, 56, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nithusha21', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 906635984, 'comment_body': 'Can there be a case where 2 (or more) state names are interchanged? If so say you rename state_1 to state_2 and rename an already existing state_2 to state_1? In which case the below logic might run into problems right?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 25, 5, 3, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nithusha21', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 906654253, 'comment_body': 'Yes, they can. But in that case, the updation of the version history will be done by the code which handles state renames above and need not be handled by the code where state property changes are being handled.

Priority of the updation process in a particular commit:
a) **Deletion** : If anything happens before deletion like change in state property or renames, then they need not be considered as the state was ultimately deleted.

b) **Addition** : If a state was added, then its `previously_edited_on_version` will be None and `state_name_in_previous_version` will also be None as it was newly added in this commit. If, in the same commit, the state undergoes property change or renames, the version history will remain same. Also, `exp_versions_diff.added_state_names` contains the latest names of the added states i.e. if a state was renamed after being added in the same commit, the list would contain the latest name.

c) **Renames** : For renames, we need to update the version number and also the state name in previous version. Hence, if any state undergoes rename and property change in the same commit, its updation of version history will be handled by the rename code and not by the state property changed code. Also, the `exp_versions_diff.old_to_new_state_names` excludes the added/deleted states.

pr_title: Milestones 1.4, 1.5, 1.6 and 1.7 (Improving the lesson creation experience): Allow users to see changes in the exploration metadata.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of N/A.
2. This PR does the following:
- Modifies the return value of `ExplorationHandler` in `reader.py` to include the new `exploration_metadata` property.
- Adds two new properties (`v1Metadata` and `v2Metadata`) in the return value of `getDiffGraphData` of `CompareVersionsService`.
- Installs the new `js-yaml` library to facilitate yaml-conversions in the frontend itself.
- Creates a new service called `YamlService` in order to use the js-yaml library.
- Creates a new service called `HistoryTabYamlConversionService` to centralize the logic for doing yaml-conversion in `StateDiffModal` and `ExplorationMetadataDiffModal`.
- Removes the `StateDiffModalBackendApiService` as it is no longer required because we are doing the conversion in the frontend itself.
- Creates the `VersionedExplorationCachingService` to cache versioned exploration data fetched from the backend.
- Makes the other changes in `HistoryTabComponent` so that users are able to see the metadata changes.
- Adds e2e tests for the subproject(A).

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

The history tab flow is working fine and user can see changes in metadata also:

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70739349/175064223-b93c17d3-24ab-4373-9764-34fcd8c5c8c9.mp4

The E2E tests are not flaky:

[Attempt 1](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/actions/runs/2601513613/attempts/1)
[Attempt 2](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/actions/runs/2601513613/attempts/2)
[Attempt 3](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/actions/runs/2601513613/attempts/3)
[Attempt 4](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/actions/runs/2601513613/attempts/4)
[Attempt 5](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/actions/runs/2601513613)

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

Notice how the data took a long time to be fetched at first due to slow network. But, due to the new caching service, the comparison graph is visible much faster when the same versions are compared the second time.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70739349/175064707-ce876e44-c402-46fc-ad59-38b218a195bc.mp4

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI in any of the files listed in rtl_css.py (i.e, those that have
a separate .rtl.css file for styling), make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Milestone 1.3 (Improving the lesson creation experience): Create the beam job.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of N/A.
2. This PR does the following:
- Creates the beam job for computing and populating ExplorationVersionHistoryModels.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

**Job can create the models from scratch**:

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70739349/177170862-c62376f3-5ee5-437c-bb98-ab3cb8aed0e6.mp4

**Job can be rerun even if random versions from the version history data are missing**:

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70739349/177170936-22bccd6c-f0db-4b94-9893-d6400697c342.mp4

**Proof of the verification job**.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70739349/181476771-5b2c84c6-2c84-4437-a150-00e50f1470e6.mp4

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI in any of the files listed in rtl_css.py (i.e, those that have
a separate .rtl.css file for styling), make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

[{'comment_id': 918719600, 'comment_body': 'Should there be a check to ensure this old_exploration is currently on the latest version of that exploration? If not there could be a fork generated in the versioning hierarchy if incorrectly used.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 8, 53, 42, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nithusha21', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 918972639, 'comment_body': 'Consider having better outputs to easily validate or invalidate a run. For example, if you output the number of version history models created, the number of existing version history models and the total number of commit log entries, it should be possible to validate that the counts add up as expected. Or that the things marked as invalid should be sent back to you (maybe the ids or something) so that you can investigate them further.  The more debugging information you get out of the job, the better :)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 13, 30, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'nithusha21', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919348978, 'comment_body': 'Done.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 19, 42, 15, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 919349198, 'comment_body': 'Improved the output now.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 12, 19, 42, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 920963982, 'comment_body': 'Why "pristine"?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 14, 9, 42, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923341130, 'comment_body': 'Can you get these using `GetModels`?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 12, 55, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923362784, 'comment_body': 'This migrates exploration to latest schema version (ditto elsewhere) is that fine?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 13, 17, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923365481, 'comment_body': 'Why do we need this?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 13, 20, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923367135, 'comment_body': "Can you please try to explain how do we generate the history? From the code I'm a bit confused.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 13, 22, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923520074, 'comment_body': 'I think its because the `old_exploration` should be in the original condition and unchanged before passing it to this function. Also, this part was earlier inside `apply_change_list` of `exp_services`. I have just refactored it so that this part of the code can also be used by the beam job.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 15, 38, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923522083, 'comment_body': 'I am not much sure if we can we do this for exploration models. Because I tried using the following query but it did not work:
```
ExplorationModel.query(ExplorationModel.version == 1)
```

However this did not work as expected. I think we can do this using GetModels at once especially because we require a specific version of the exploration and not the latest one.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 15, 40, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923524310, 'comment_body': 'Yes, that should be fine as there is a safeguard applied earlier that if the exploration cannot be converted, then we will not consider this exploration for version history computation as for applying change list to exploration, we need to have the exploration domain object corresponding to the model.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 15, 43, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923550016, 'comment_body': 'Also, `apply_change_list_to_exploration` requires the exploration domain object.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 16, 6, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923560420, 'comment_body': 'Without this, I face the error `NDB calls must be made in context established by google.cloud.ndb.Client.context.`

It is because new models are being created in this step.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 16, 17, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923573019, 'comment_body': "This happens in the following steps:

1. All the exploration models at latest version, at first version and all the commit log and existing version history models are fetched first.
2. We then group all these models under the exploration ids. After grouping, the groups are validated under `_filter_valid_model_group` and then reformatted for their easier access (i.e. sorting the commit logs and existing version history models according to version).
3. Now, the history is generated for each exploration. The history is generated in the same way as done in `exp_services` i.e. take the version history of the previous version and update it according to the change list.
4. If version is 1, then no state or the exploration metadata would have a 'previously edited version', hence, we are setting them as None when the version is 1.
5. Otherwise, we are generating the new version history by taking the previous version history similar to what is done in `exp_services.update_version_history`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 16, 30, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923574590, 'comment_body': 'Also, if revert commit is present in the exploration at any version, it needs to be handled differently.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 16, 32, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923576711, 'comment_body': 'One more thing that we check is that if the version history model for a particular version already exists, if so, then we just modify it with the correct data. Otherwise, we create the new model for every version.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 16, 33, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923651674, 'comment_body': "Why it didn't work?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 17, 44, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923653088, 'comment_body': '"pristine" is a bit hard to understand, it is not common word, can we use something more understandable?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 17, 45, 37, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923700546, 'comment_body': 'I think we cannot get a specific version of (in this case v1) of all explorations or any other similar versioned model. This query would instead fetch the exploration models whose latest version is 1 and not the v1 of all the exploration models.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 18, 38, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923701797, 'comment_body': 'Any version other than the latest one is fetched by reconstituting from the snapshot id in case of VersionedModels.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 18, 39, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 923701932, 'comment_body': 'Done.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 18, 18, 39, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 925537144, 'comment_body': 'Then you can fetch some of the snapshots and reconstitute it yourself. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 20, 12, 18, 51, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 925537615, 'comment_body': 'Ok!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 20, 12, 19, 23, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 926440791, 'comment_body': "This can be done before this loop, right? The we don't need the if-else", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 21, 9, 7, 34, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vojtechjelinek', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927757345, 'comment_body': 'I have done this using get_multi call. Please take a look. If we want to do this using GetModels, we would have to fetch all the snapshot models first and then filter them.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 22, 15, 20, 6, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'soumyo123-prog', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 927757901, 'comment_body': 'This would cause fetching of much unnecessary data. pr_title: Milestone 1.8 (Improving the lesson creation experience): Make changes in the controller layer and also create the backend api service.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of N/A.
2. This PR does the following:
- Adds a fetcher in `exp_fetchers` to get the version history data.
- Adds two new URLs and their handlers in `reader.py` to fetch version history data for exploration state and metadata.
- Adds the `VersionHistoryBackendApiService` to fetch the version history data from the backend.
- Adds a constant in `constants.ts` which will prevent the frontend to fetch the version history data for now. This constant is not used in this PR and but will be required later on.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

No proof of changes needed because this PR just adds controllers and services. Also, all the backend and frontend tests for the controllers and services are passing.

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI in any of the files listed in rtl_css.py (i.e, those that have
a separate .rtl.css file for styling), make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of N/A.
2. This PR does the following:
- This PR fixes the commit commands of an exploration by adding an 'add_state' command for the state 'END' in the commit commands of version 3 of the exploration. This is necessary in order to compute the version history for the exploration.

pr_title: Milestone 2.1 (Improving the lesson creation experience): Frontend changes for users to be able to explore the version history.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of N/A.
2. This PR does the following:
- Creates the StateVersionHistory and MetadataVersionHistory modals to show the diff between different version.
- Creates VersionHistoryService to store the fetched version history data on the frontend.
- Makes the necessary changes in exploration editor tab and exploration settings tab components to show the button for exploring version history.

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70739349/200161640-8f7db8fa-689f-4244-a641-8cbd2c7e4bf1.mp4



#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI, make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Make-a-pull-request).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia's-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-CI-checks-fail-on-your-PR).
